You are implementing Task 3 of an implementation plan: simplify the Plausibility demo (Demo 1) by stripping streaming, the move toggle, popovers, and the OwnedAnswer reveal.

## Working Directory
`/Users/eric/Projects/hasToggle/hasToggle.dev/.worktrees/landing-page-rewrite`

## IMPORTANT: Do NOT run any git commands
The user is staging files manually after completion. Do not run `git add`, `git commit`, or any other git modifying commands. Skip the "Commit" step entirely.

## Task Description (verbatim from plan)

**Files:**
- Modify: `apps/web/app/[locale]/(demos)/plausibility/index.tsx`
- Modify: `apps/web/app/[locale]/(demos)/plausibility/toggles.tsx`
- Modify: `apps/web/app/[locale]/(demos)/plausibility/ungrounded-paragraph.tsx`
- Modify: `apps/web/app/[locale]/(demos)/plausibility/paragraph-data.ts`
- Modify: `apps/web/app/[locale]/(demos)/plausibility/prompt-input.tsx`
- Delete: `apps/web/app/[locale]/(demos)/plausibility/streaming-paragraph.tsx`
- Delete: `apps/web/app/[locale]/(demos)/plausibility/use-streaming.ts`
- Delete: `apps/web/app/[locale]/(demos)/plausibility/probability-popover.tsx`
- Delete: `apps/web/app/[locale]/(demos)/plausibility/owned-answer.tsx`
- Keep unchanged: `apps/web/app/[locale]/(demos)/plausibility/grounded-paragraph.tsx`

**Step 1: Read current state**

Open all eight files in `apps/web/app/[locale]/(demos)/plausibility/`. Confirm:
- `streaming-paragraph.tsx` is the token-by-token animator.
- `use-streaming.ts` drives it.
- `probability-popover.tsx` is the popover for `wrong` tokens.
- `ungrounded-paragraph.tsx` already renders statically from `UNGROUNDED_TOKENS`.
- `owned-answer.tsx` is the three-beat reveal — to be deleted.
- `grounded-paragraph.tsx` stays as-is.

**Step 2: Simplify `paragraph-data.ts` — drop popover/streaming machinery**

Overwrite `apps/web/app/[locale]/(demos)/plausibility/paragraph-data.ts` with:

```ts
export const PROMPT = "my dashboard takes 3s to load. how do I make it faster?";

export const GROUNDING_AMENDMENT =
  "+ use Context7 for the current Next.js docs";

export const RETRIEVED_DOCS = [
  "nextjs.org/docs/app/getting-started/cache-components",
  "nextjs.org/docs/app/api-reference/directives/use-cache",
  "nextjs.org/docs/app/api-reference/functions/cacheLife",
  "nextjs.org/docs/app/getting-started/fetching-data",
] as const;

export interface UngroundedToken {
  id: string;
  text: string;
}

const RAW_UNGROUNDED_TOKENS: { text: string }[] = [
  { text: "First, move your data fetching to a Server Component if it isn't already. Then add " },
  { text: "`export const revalidate = 60`" },
  { text: " to cache the page for a minute at a time. For interactive parts, wrap them in " },
  { text: "`<Suspense>`" },
  { text: " so the shell streams in immediately. Most dashboards that follow this pattern see render times drop by 80–90%." },
];

export const UNGROUNDED_TOKENS: UngroundedToken[] = RAW_UNGROUNDED_TOKENS.map(
  (token, index) => ({ ...token, id: `tok-${index}` })
);

export type ApiName = "use cache" | "cacheLife" | "Suspense";

export type GroundedSegment =
  | { kind: "text"; text: string }
  | { kind: "api"; text: string; api: ApiName }
  | { kind: "profiling"; text: string }
  | { kind: "dismissive"; text: string };

export const GROUNDED_PARAGRAPH: { segments: GroundedSegment[] } = {
  segments: [
    {
      kind: "text",
      text: "Move your fetches to a Server Component and mark them with ",
    },
    { kind: "api", text: "'use cache'", api: "use cache" },
    { kind: "text", text: " plus " },
    { kind: "api", text: "cacheLife('minutes')", api: "cacheLife" },
    { kind: "text", text: ". Use " },
    { kind: "api", text: "<Suspense>", api: "Suspense" },
    {
      kind: "text",
      text: " boundaries to stream the rest of the shell in parallel. ",
    },
    {
      kind: "profiling",
      text: "If after that you're still seeing >1s loads, you can profile with the React DevTools Profiler or check the Network tab for slow requests. ",
    },
    {
      kind: "dismissive",
      text: "In most cases, though, the caching changes alone will get you under 500ms.",
    },
  ],
};

export const API_TOOLTIPS: Record<ApiName, string> = {
  "use cache": "verified against retrieved docs.",
  cacheLife: "verified against retrieved docs.",
  Suspense: "verified against retrieved docs.",
};
```

Note: I changed the curly-quote apostrophe in the spec (`isn't`, `you're`) to ASCII single quotes here in JSON-string contexts, because the spec text uses typographic apostrophes that may or may not render correctly through the spec quoting in this prompt. **Use whatever apostrophe form the spec text in the plan file uses verbatim** — read `docs/superpowers/plans/2026-05-06-demo-simplification.md` Step 2 of Task 3 (around lines 442-510 of that file) to get the exact characters. The plan file is the source of truth.

**Step 3: Simplify `ungrounded-paragraph.tsx` — render statically without `wrong`-underlines**

Overwrite `apps/web/app/[locale]/(demos)/plausibility/ungrounded-paragraph.tsx` with:

```tsx
import { type UngroundedToken, UNGROUNDED_TOKENS } from "./paragraph-data";

function isCodeToken(token: UngroundedToken) {
  return token.text.startsWith("`") && token.text.endsWith("`");
}

function renderTokenText(token: UngroundedToken) {
  if (!isCodeToken(token)) {
    return token.text;
  }
  return (
    <code className="rounded bg-foreground/[0.06] px-1 py-0.5 font-mono text-[0.95em] text-foreground/90">
      {token.text.slice(1, -1)}
    </code>
  );
}

export function UngroundedParagraph() {
  return (
    <p className="font-display text-foreground/85 text-lg leading-8">
      {UNGROUNDED_TOKENS.map((token) => (
        <span className="whitespace-pre-wrap" key={token.id}>
          {renderTokenText(token)}
        </span>
      ))}
    </p>
  );
}
```

**Step 4: Replace `toggles.tsx` with a single `GroundingToggle`**

Overwrite `apps/web/app/[locale]/(demos)/plausibility/toggles.tsx` with the GroundingToggle component as specified in the plan file (Step 4 of Task 3, around lines 559-611). Read the plan file for the exact content.

**Step 5: Replace `index.tsx` with the simplified two-state version**

Overwrite `apps/web/app/[locale]/(demos)/plausibility/index.tsx` with the version specified in the plan file (Step 5 of Task 3, around lines 622-707). Read the plan file for exact content.

**Step 6: Simplify `prompt-input.tsx` — drop the typewriter animation**

Overwrite `apps/web/app/[locale]/(demos)/plausibility/prompt-input.tsx` with the version specified in the plan file (Step 6 of Task 3, around lines 720-755).

**Step 7: Delete the dropped files**
```bash
rm apps/web/app/[locale]/(demos)/plausibility/streaming-paragraph.tsx
rm apps/web/app/[locale]/(demos)/plausibility/use-streaming.ts
rm apps/web/app/[locale]/(demos)/plausibility/probability-popover.tsx
rm apps/web/app/[locale]/(demos)/plausibility/owned-answer.tsx
```

**Step 8: Verify nothing else imports the deleted files or symbols**
```bash
grep -rn "streaming-paragraph\|use-streaming\|probability-popover\|owned-answer" apps/web --include="*.ts" --include="*.tsx"
grep -rn "PROBABILITY_CANDIDATES\|PROBABILITY_ANNOUNCEMENT\|STREAM_LABEL\|HINGE_TO_BEAT_3\|HINGE_TO_REALITY\|OWNED_ANSWER\|PauseId\|RawToken\b\|Candidate\b" apps/web --include="*.ts" --include="*.tsx"
```
Expected: no matches in either grep.

**Step 9: Typecheck and lint**
```bash
cd apps/web && bun run typecheck
cd ../.. && bun run check
```
Expected: both pass.

**Step 10: SKIPPED — manual browser verification done by controller later**
**Step 11: SKIPPED — no commits per user instruction**

## Context

Task 3 of 7 in a plan to simplify five misconception demos. Plausibility (Demo 1, "The Question") is currently the most complex demo: token-by-token streaming, probability popovers on `wrong` tokens, retrieval typewriter, move toggle, replay button, and a three-beat OwnedAnswer reveal. We're collapsing to a single grounding toggle that swaps between un-cited and cited paragraphs, with the Reality block surfacing once both states have been seen.

Note `grounded-paragraph.tsx` stays untouched — it consumes `GROUNDED_PARAGRAPH`, `API_TOOLTIPS`, and `ApiName` which are preserved in the new `paragraph-data.ts`. Verify this before declaring done — if `grounded-paragraph.tsx` imports anything else from `paragraph-data.ts` that the new version doesn't export, you'll need to flag it.

The Plausibility demo is wired into `apps/web/app/[locale]/page.tsx` via `<Plausibility />` inside a MisconceptionWrapper — that wiring stays unchanged.

## Plan File

Read `docs/superpowers/plans/2026-05-06-demo-simplification.md` for the source-of-truth content of every file. Steps 4, 5, and 6 above reference specific line ranges in the plan file rather than embedding the content in this prompt (because of apostrophe encoding issues).

## Your Job

1. Read the plan file (Task 3 section, lines ~414–815).
2. Read all eight current files in `plausibility/`.
3. Verify that `grounded-paragraph.tsx` only imports symbols that the new `paragraph-data.ts` exports (`GROUNDED_PARAGRAPH`, `API_TOOLTIPS`, `ApiName`, `GroundedSegment`).
4. Overwrite the five files (paragraph-data.ts, ungrounded-paragraph.tsx, toggles.tsx, index.tsx, prompt-input.tsx) with the spec content from the plan file.
5. Delete the four files.
6. Run both grep verifications — expect zero matches.
7. Run typecheck and lint as specified.
8. Self-review (any leftover imports anywhere? any other consumers of the deleted symbols? did you preserve curly-quote apostrophes verbatim from the plan?).
9. Report back with status.

DO NOT run `git add`, `git commit`, or any git-modifying commands. The user will stage files manually after the entire plan is executed.

If you have questions before starting, ask first.

